題名: 斜張型盆地的構造-地層耦合系統發育模型-中非裂谷研究(I)
其他題名: Evolutionary Model of Structure-Stratigraphy Coupling System in Oblique Rift Basins-Study of Central African Rifts
作者: 楊耿明林慶偉
貢獻者: 地球科學系
關鍵詞: 中非裂谷斜張型盆地石油盆地構造地層Central African RiftsOblique rift basinPetroleum basinTectonostratigraphy
日期: 2012
上傳時間: 2013-06-10 14:29:03  (UTC+8)
摘要: 在全球石油盆地的分類上，斜張型盆地的構造單元和地層內已發現油氣田數目佔全球總數的相當可觀的比例，也被列為二十一世紀從事國外油氣探勘重要潛能盆地，該類石油盆地是不容忽視的對象。近年來，臺灣中油公司在國外的探勘活動及探勘研究計劃中，與大陸張裂作用和走向滑移斷層作用相關的中非裂谷被列入下一階段重要探勘標。有關與大陸張裂作用和大規模走向滑移斷層作用相關的構造-地層研究及模型，可以提供從事此一類型石油盆地的探勘所需的參考性基礎架構。本計劃擬根據以往從事臺灣西部和北安地斯山前陸地區的盆地架構研究方法和成果，配合臺灣中油公司於國外的探勘活動以及探採研究所年度計畫，和臺灣中油公司合作，建立斜張型石油盆地內構造和地層耦合系統發育的理論模型。本計劃將從事中非裂谷的盆地架構和構造型式的模型建立，探討該構造盆地演化的歷史以及岩相的時空分佈。本計劃的研究成果將提供臺灣中油公司從事中非裂谷油氣探勘的參考。In the classification of global petroleum basins the number of discovered oil and gas fields in the structural settings and basins that are related with oblique rift basins is significant. Therefore, the petroleum basins in such type of basin cannot be ignored when engaging oversea hydrocarbon exploration. Recently, prospects in Central African Rifts that are highly related with oblique rifting are targeted by oversea exploration and research project of exploration undertaken by CPC Corporation, Taiwan. Studies and models concerning the structure and stratigraphy in oblique rift basins should provide reference as the very basic framework for the exploration in this kind of petroleum basins. This project attempts to establish some evolutionary models of syn-tectonic structure-stratigraphy coupling system in the petroleum basins formed by oblique rifting. This project will be based on the methods and results that stem from the previous basin architecture studies on the extensional tectonics in western Taiwan and on the foreland areas in northern Andes. This project will also be concordant with the project of exploration and annual research undertaken by CPC, Taiwan, on prospects in some basins of the Central African Rifts. The main targets are to establish the models of basin architecture and structural styles in Central African Rifts and to investigate the basin evolution and the time-spatial distribution of lithofacies in the basins. The study results of this project will be fed back as the reference to the exploration undertaken by CPC, Taiwan, on the Central African Rifts.
相關連結: http://grbsearch.stpi.narl.org.tw/GRB/result.jsp?id=2393441&plan_no=NSC101-ET-E006-008-ET&plan_year=101&projkey=PB10101-3919&target=plan&highStr=*&check=0&pnchDesc=%E6%96%9C%E5%BC%B5%E5%9E%8B%E7%9B%86%E5%9C%B0%E7%9A%84%E6%A7%8B%E9%80%A0-%E5%9C%B0%E5%B1%A4%E8%80%A6%E5%90%88%E7%B3%BB%E7%B5%B1%E7%99%BC%E8%82%B2%E6%A8%A1%E5%9E%8B-%E4%B8%AD%E9%9D%9E%E8%A3%82%E8%B0%B7%E7%A0%94%E7%A9%B6%28I%29
描述: 計畫編號:NSC101-ET-E006-008-ET執行機構:國立成功大學地球科學系研究期間:2012-01~2012-12
